OL,3,CWhere to get help if you are suffering
OL,4,Cwith domestic abuse
OL,6,FYou can contact the National Domestic
OL,7,FViolence Helpline on 0808 2000 247.
OL,9,FA female adviser will listen to you in
OL,10,Fconfidence, and support you in making
OL,11,Fdecisions about the future. The
OL,12,Fadviser can also help you find a
OL,13,Frefuge place or other specialist
OL,14,Fservices.
OL,16,FHelp for women from minority
OL,17,Fbackgrounds
OL,19,FThe Angelou Centre in Newcastle upon
OL,20,FTyne can help arrange refuge
OL,21,Faccommodation.
